      <p>where <italic>MAD</italic> = <italic>m</italic>(|<italic>x</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub>−<italic>m</italic><sub><italic>x</italic></sub>|), the median (m) of the absolute deviations from the data’s median (m<sub><italic>x</italic></sub>).</p>
    </sec>
